<task id="R7-111" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Wire ITemplateEngine into PlaybookOrchestrationService + carry RunContext.NodeOutputs to subsequent nodes</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>11</wave>
    <estimated-effort>3-4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, code-impl, ai, refactoring, wave-11</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies .cs (PlaybookOrchestrationService + RunContext); tags include `bff-api`; has 7+ steps; downstream tasks 112/113/114/115 depend on this. FULL per task-execute Step 0.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>110</dependencies>
    <blocks>112, 113, 114</blocks>
    <fr-coverage>FR-15 (orchestrator now resolves node-output references — prerequisite for /narrate end-to-end)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    **FINAL REVISION 2026-06-29 — Option B (operator-approved after deeper inspection of
    PromptSchemaRenderer + JPS schema).**

    LAYER 1 (universal — every executor): extract `PlaybookTemplateContextBuilder.Build(runContext)`
    and wire orchestrator's `ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` to use `ITemplateEngine.Render` with it.
    Every executor's configJson gets `{{X}}` substitution at the string level (NodeOutputs +
    Parameters + run bag context). Existing `LoadKnowledgeNodeExecutor` + `ReturnResponseNodeExecutor`
    BuildTemplateContext methods refactored to call the shared helper.

    LAYER 2 (AI-shared — structured Input section, NOT embedded placeholders): finalize the
    half-built `InputSection.Parameters` field in PromptSchema. Extend `PromptSchemaRenderer.Render`
    to accept `JsonElement? runtimeInput` parameter and render a new "## Input\n{json}" section
    between Context and Document. AI executors (AiCompletion + AiAnalysis) extract resolved
    `inputBinding` from configJson, package as JsonElement, pass to renderer as `runtimeInput`.

    KEY DESIGN PROPERTY (operator-required): the Action JPS body (instruction.role/task/constraints/context)
    stays PURE INSTRUCTIONS — no `{{X}}` substitution for data. Data lives in its own structured
    "## Input" section the LLM clearly sees. This decouples prompt-instruction authoring from
    data-shape authoring, enabling future narrative-output consumers (Insight Engine Matter
    summaries, work assignment briefings, project status, document review, etc.) to be authored
    as 1 Action JPS + 1 playbook + 1 destination-field — zero new C# per consumer.

    Documentation deliverable spawns as T111a (architecture doc + maker guide) — operator
    requirement for Insights Engine + many other areas.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in C# generics, Handlebars.NET, and the BFF playbook
    orchestrator. Follow ADRs strictly. Match the existing TemplateEngine's "graceful on missing"
    contract — don't throw on unresolved bindings.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookOrchestrationService` injects `ITemplateEngine`, calls `Render` (not literal Replace)
    against a merged Parameters + NodeOutputs context dict. `RunContext` carries `NodeOutputs`.
    Subsequent-node configJson resolution now sees prior nodes' OutputVariable values. xUnit
    tests prove behavior. Build passes; existing orchestrator tests pass (no regression).
  </goal>

